Sentencas: 8 mol % yttria stabilized zirconia (8 YSZ) is widely used as an electrolyte material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) at high temperatures, but its poor sinterability causes complications of the cell fabrication processes, increasing manufacturing costs significantly.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper

Sentencas: In this study, a low-temperature co-firing process for the YSZ-based SOFCs is developed by adding the small amount of Cu to each of YSZ electrolytes and anodes.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper

Sentencas: The cells are successfully fabricated without any distortions or cracks.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper

Sentencas: The cell is about 1.011 V at 850 degrees C in open circuit voltage (OCV), which is reasonable despite of the co-firing process even at 1250 degrees C.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper

Sentencas: The maximum power density is 0.71 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, which has similar performance of a conventional cell fabricated by multi-step process.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper

Sentencas: Overall, the co-firing process using Cu can become promising for cost-effective fabrication process of the SOFCs except the problems related to the cathode.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-firing process of solid oxide fuel cells by a trace of copper
